Sessions are done with $_SESSION
Cookies are done with $_COOKIE

Sessions have the following advantages
- Data is stored on the server, not the user's PC
- More data can be stored (and retrieved from the database)
- Can be used without Cookies

Cookies have the following advantages
- Easier to program
- Doesn't use much server stuff
- You can program their expiration date


Most web applications use Sessions because of the sheer amount of info you need to save. If you're writing 
an application with very little bits of info to store, use cookies